description:
Non material amendment of planning permission P090206 dated 1st April 2009 for the 'Redevelopment of Regent Quarter Block D, comprising of part demolition, part conversion of existing buildings  and erection of part 2 to 6 storey buildings to accommodate 5439m² business (Use Class B1), 175m² restaurant (Use Class A3) and 54 residential units (19x1, 30x2 and 5x3 beds), with 135 cycle spaces, 3 disabled spaces and associated landscaping'. The amendments include:
a) Creation of link between the basement of Buildings D2, D3 and D4 and the installation of a new plant room in the north-east corner of the basement to Building D2;
b) Installation of hoist in the lightwell serving Building D2 within the Wharfdale Road elevation;
c) Relocation of the entrance to Building D2 and erection of a canopy over the new entrance;
d) Internal alteration to the former entrance lobby of Building D2 to infill the double height space; 
e) Construction of a link at basement to fourth floor levels between 42-50 York Way and Building D2 including the provision of four openings within the proposed building link; and
f) Formation of the main entrance to Block D4 (Stable building) from the western courtyard (as approved under Listed Building Consent ref: P120405, dated 13/04/2012).
